other convicts and Puritan conduct books. It thus offers scholars of literature, drama, art and history a unique opportunity to consider the literary, visual and rhetorical representation of motherhood in the context of a discussion of familiar and less familiar dramatic texts.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 06. Mrz 2024) 4aShakespeare 2018. 7aPERFORMING ARTS / Theater / History & Criticism.2bisacsh  aEnglish drama.  aMother's Legacies.  acomedies.  aearly modern dramatists.  ahistory plays.  amelodrama.  amidwifery manuals.  amother figure.  aromances.  atragedies.1 aDunworth, Felicity, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertManchester University Press 1986 - 2013 eBook Packagez978311128363040uhttps://doi.org/10.7765/978184779289140uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781847792891423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781847792891/original  a978-3-11-128363-0  Manchester University Press 1986 - 2013 eBook Packagec1986d2013  aGBV-deGruyter-alles